 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 to `review` status. This has happened 76 consecutive times now. The retrospective should emphasize the urgent need to stop Ralph and the massive token waste.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — no-op session #76, state corruption fix applied, no real work done\n2. **Issues analysis** — the Ralph state corruption loop is the only issue, now at 76 occurrences\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report, emphasize waste from no-op sessions\n4. **What went well** — state corruption detected and fixed quickly\n5. **What went wrong** — Ralph still running, 76th consecutive waste of tokens\n6. **Lessons learned** — autonomous loops need kill switches\n7. **Action items** — STOP RALPH immediately\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md.\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"af4ff92d1a0137b2d","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md`.\n\n**Summary:**\n- Appended NO-OP session #76 retrospective with `---` separator\n- Cost analysis: $810.72 total, ~$200-300 (25-37%) wasted on 76 no-op sessions\n- The \"unknown\" story bucket at $208.05 is the clearest waste signal -- it is almost entirely no-op session overhead\n- Single action item that matters: **stop Ralph immediately**. Everything else is secondary. The sprint is done. 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics. There is nothing left to do."}],"totalDurationMs":72858,"totalTokens":34032,"totalToolUseCount":7,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1945,"cache_read_input_tokens":31906,"output_tokens":180,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fet